Top CEO's are converging bin Rwanda’s capital Kigali to attend the 7th edition of the Africa CEO’s forum. The event is usually an avenue for CEO’s to network at an executive level with peers from different countries in Africa. The forum brings together 4 African heads of state, 700 CEOs, and 1,800 participants from 70 countries. Today's key issues saw leaders discuss how to boost regional integration with a focus on public-private partnerships.